GitHub Pages is a static website hosting service that allows developers to publish websites directly from a GitHub repository.

Q2. What types of sites can be hosted on GitHub Pages?

Static websites

Portfolio websites

Documentation

Blogs

Frontend project demos

Q3. What file is required for a GitHub Pages homepage?
index.html


or

index.md

Q4. Can GitHub Pages host backend applications?

No. It only supports static content like HTML, CSS, and JavaScript.

Q5. What is the difference between User Site and Project Site?
Type	Repository Name	URL
User Site	username.github.io	username.github.io
Project Site	any name	username.github.io/project-name
Q6. How does deployment happen in GitHub Pages?

Deployment occurs automatically when code is pushed to the selected branch (usually main).

